---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Projects | Rishab" description="Showcase of my engineering, development, and design work.">
	<section class="projects-page">
		<div class="container">
			<div class="page-header">
				<h1 class="page-title text-gradient">Projects</h1>
				<p class="page-desc">A gallery of systems, applications, and tools I have engineered.</p>
			</div>

			<div class="projects-grid">
				<!-- Project 1: ADAPT -->
				<div class="project-card glass">
					<div class="project-card-header">
						<span class="project-tag">Python</span>
						<span class="project-tag">PyTorch</span>
						<span class="project-tag">ML Parallelism</span>
					</div>
					<h3>ADAPT - Automated Parallel Training for ML Workloads on Heterogeneous Systems</h3>
					<p>An implementation of an efficient, adaptive, and optimized parallel training strategy. Utilizes Data, Model, and Pipeline Parallel training formats, with experimental support for Tensor Parallel training. Automates training script layouts by evaluating systems-level cost functions on heterogeneous clusters.</p>
					<div class="project-links">
						<a href="https://github.com/Rishabkashyap14" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="project-link">
							<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M15 22v-4a4.8 4.8 0 0 0-1-3.5c3 0 6-2 6-5.5.08-1.25-.27-2.48-1-3.5.28-1.15.28-2.35 0-3.5 0 0-1 0-3 1.5-2.64-.5-5.36-.5-8 0C6 2 5 2 5 2c-.3 1.15-.3 2.35 0 3.5A5.403 5.403 0 0 0 4 9c0 3.5 3 5.5 6 5.5-.39.49-.68 1.05-.85 1.65-.17.6-.22 1.23-.15 1.85v4"></path></svg>
							Repository
						</a>
						<span class="project-status">Thesis Research</span>
					</div>
				</div>

				<!-- Project 2: Malicious URL Classifier -->
				<div class="project-card glass">
					<div class="project-card-header">
						<span class="project-tag">Python</span>
						<span class="project-tag">Scikit-Learn</span>
						<span class="project-tag">Ensemble Methods</span>
					</div>
					<h3>Classification of Malicious URLs using Ensemble Machine Learning</h3>
					<p>Built a cascading classifier utilizing 7 machine learning models to detect malicious URLs. Six base models evaluate independent feature sets (domain attributes, symbol frequencies, DOM structure, and text content), passing predictions to a final decision tree ensemble. Published at the IEEE-CSDE'21 conference.</p>
					<div class="project-links">
						<a href="https://github.com/Rishabkashyap14/URL-Classifier" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="project-link">
							<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M15 22v-4a4.8 4.8 0 0 0-1-3.5c3 0 6-2 6-5.5.08-1.25-.27-2.48-1-3.5.28-1.15.28-2.35 0-3.5 0 0-1 0-3 1.5-2.64-.5-5.36-.5-8 0C6 2 5 2 5 2c-.3 1.15-.3 2.35 0 3.5A5.403 5.403 0 0 0 4 9c0 3.5 3 5.5 6 5.5-.39.49-.68 1.05-.85 1.65-.17.6-.22 1.23-.15 1.85v4"></path></svg>
							Source Code
						</a>
					</div>
				</div>

				<!-- Project 3: Movie Success Predictor -->
				<div class="project-card glass">
					<div class="project-card-header">
						<span class="project-tag">R</span>
						<span class="project-tag">Python</span>
						<span class="project-tag">Data Analysis</span>
					</div>
					<h3>Movie Success Prediction using Machine Learning</h3>
					<p>An exploratory study comparing statistical approaches to predict box-office success. Conducted extensive data cleaning and analysis to establish correlation factors (actors, budget, rating, director), implementing multiple models on data subsets. Published at the MLDS'21 conference and in the IJAIA'21 journal.</p>
					<div class="project-links">
						<a href="https://github.com/Rishabkashyap14/Movie-success-predictor" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="project-link">
							<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M15 22v-4a4.8 4.8 0 0 0-1-3.5c3 0 6-2 6-5.5.08-1.25-.27-2.48-1-3.5.28-1.15.28-2.35 0-3.5 0 0-1 0-3 1.5-2.64-.5-5.36-.5-8 0C6 2 5 2 5 2c-.3 1.15-.3 2.35 0 3.5A5.403 5.403 0 0 0 4 9c0 3.5 3 5.5 6 5.5-.39.49-.68 1.05-.85 1.65-.17.6-.22 1.23-.15 1.85v4"></path></svg>
							Source Code
						</a>
					</div>
				</div>

				<!-- Project 4: Habitable Exoplanets -->
				<div class="project-card glass">
					<div class="project-card-header">
						<span class="project-tag">Python</span>
						<span class="project-tag">ML Models</span>
						<span class="project-tag">NASA Kepler</span>
					</div>
					<h3>Classification of Habitable Exoplanets</h3>
					<p>Developed model layouts to identify habitable exoplanets based on NASA's Kepler dataset. Extracted planetary and host star properties (mass, radiation, orbit, composition) and evaluated model recall profiles to establish optimal predictors for astrobiological habitability.</p>
					<div class="project-links">
						<a href="https://github.com/Rishabkashyap14/CSE_575_Habitability" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="project-link">
							<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M15 22v-4a4.8 4.8 0 0 0-1-3.5c3 0 6-2 6-5.5.08-1.25-.27-2.48-1-3.5.28-1.15.28-2.35 0-3.5 0 0-1 0-3 1.5-2.64-.5-5.36-.5-8 0C6 2 5 2 5 2c-.3 1.15-.3 2.35 0 3.5A5.403 5.403 0 0 0 4 9c0 3.5 3 5.5 6 5.5-.39.49-.68 1.05-.85 1.65-.17.6-.22 1.23-.15 1.85v4"></path></svg>
							Source Code
						</a>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>

<style>
	.projects-page {
		padding: 5rem 0;
	}

	.page-header {
		text-align: center;
		margin-bottom: 5rem;
	}

	.page-title {
		font-size: 3rem;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
		font-weight: 800;
	}

	.page-desc {
		color: var(--text-secondary);
		font-size: 1.15rem;
		max-width: 600px;
		margin: 0 auto;
	}

	/* Projects Grid */
	.projects-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		gap: 2.5rem;
	}

	.project-card {
		padding: 2.5rem;
		border-radius: 20px;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 1.25rem;
		border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
		transition: transform var(--transition-smooth), border-color var(--transition-smooth), box-shadow var(--transition-smooth);
	}

	.project-card:hover {
		transform: translateY(-5px);
		border-color: var(--accent-light);
		box-shadow: 0 12px 35px rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.08);
	}

	.project-card-header {
		display: flex;
		gap: 0.5rem;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
	}

	.project-tag {
		font-size: 0.75rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem;
		background: var(--bg-primary);
		border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
		border-radius: 9999px;
		color: var(--text-secondary);
	}

	.project-card h3 {
		font-size: 1.4rem;
		color: var(--text-primary);
	}

	.project-card p {
		font-size: 1rem;
		color: var(--text-secondary);
		line-height: 1.6;
		flex-grow: 1;
	}

	.project-links {
		display: flex;
		gap: 1.25rem;
		margin-top: 0.5rem;
	}

	.project-link {
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: var(--accent-light);
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 0.35rem;
	}

	.project-link:hover {
		color: var(--accent);
	}

	.project-link.disabled {
		color: var(--text-muted);
		pointer-events: none;
		cursor: default;
	}

	/* Responsive */
	@media (max-width: 900px) {
		.projects-grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
			gap: 1.75rem;
		}
	}

	@media (max-width: 768px) {
		.projects-page {
			padding: 4rem 0;
		}

		.page-title {
			font-size: 2.5rem;
		}

		.project-card {
			padding: 1.75rem 1.5rem;
		}
	}
</style>
